TITLE: Creating a Custom Dagger Function in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript code defines a Dagger Function named 'getUser' that uses a container to make an HTTP request to a random user API and return the parsed result.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dagger/dagger.git/blob/main/docs/current_docs/api/custom-functions.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Container, dag } from "@dagger.io/dagger"

export default async function getUser(): Promise<string> {
  return await dag.container().from("alpine:latest")
    .withExec(["apk", "add", "curl", "jq"])
    .withExec([
      "sh", "-c",
      "curl -s https://randomuser.me/api/ | jq -r '.results[0].name'",
    ])
    .stdout()
}
```

