TITLE: Binding Services in Dagger Functions (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript code demonstrates creating an HTTP service and using it in another Dagger Function. It defines two methods: 'httpService' which returns a Service, and 'get' which binds the service and accesses it.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dagger/dagger.git/blob/main/docs/current_docs/api/services.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { dag, Container, Service } from "@dagger.io/dagger"

export default class MyModule {
  async httpService(): Promise<Service> {
    return dag.container().from("nginx:1.25-alpine").withExposedPort(80).asService()
  }

  async get(): Promise<string> {
    return dag
      .container()
      .from("alpine")
      .withServiceBinding("www", await this.httpService())
      .withExec(["wget", "-O", "-", "http://www", "--timeout", "1"])
      .stdout()
  }
}
```

