TITLE: Calling Dagger Function in GitHub Actions (Standard Runner)
DESCRIPTION: This YAML snippet demonstrates how to call a Dagger Function on a standard GitHub runner in a GitHub Actions workflow. It uses the 'Dagger for GitHub' action to execute a simple greeting function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dagger/dagger.git/blob/main/docs/current_docs/ci/integrations/github-actions.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
name: dagger
on:
  push:
    branches: [ main ]

jobs:
  dagger:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - name: Checkout
        uses: actions/checkout@v3
      - name: Dagger
        uses: dagger/dagger-for-github@v5
        with:
          version: "0.9.3"
          cmds: |    
            project init
            project update
            call hello --name world
        env:
          DAGGER_CLOUD_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.DAGGER_CLOUD_TOKEN }}
```

