TITLE: Creating a Custom Dagger Module for Google Cloud Run Deployment in Go
DESCRIPTION: This Go code snippet creates a custom Dagger module that uses the google-cloud-run module to deploy an application to Google Cloud Run. It defines a 'deploy' function that takes project details, image information, and credentials as inputs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dagger/dagger.git/blob/main/docs/current_docs/ci/integrations/google-cloud-run.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
package main

import (
	"context"
	"fmt"

	"dagger.io/dagger"
	"github.com/vvaswani/daggerverse/google-cloud-run"
)

type MyModule struct {}

func (m *MyModule) Deploy(
	ctx context.Context,
	projectName string,
	serviceLocation string,
	imageAddress string,
	servicePort int,
	credential *dagger.Secret,
) (string, error) {
	gcr := google_cloud_run.New()

	service, err := gcr.CreateService(
		ctx,
		projectName,
		serviceLocation,
		imageAddress,
		servicePort,
		credential,
	)
	if err != nil {
		return "", err
	}

	return fmt.Sprintf("Application deployed to %s", service), nil
}
```

