TITLE: Creating Interdependent Services (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: This PHP code shows how to create two interdependent services with custom hostnames. It defines methods to create service A and service B, which can communicate with each other using predefined hostnames.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dagger/dagger.git/blob/main/docs/current_docs/api/services.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace MyModule;

use Dagger\Container;
use Dagger\Module;
use Dagger\Service;

class MyModule extends Module
{
    public function serviceA(): Service
    {
        return $this->dag->container()
            ->from('nginx:alpine')
            ->withNewFile('/usr/share/nginx/html/index.html', ['contents' => 'Hello from Service A!'])
            ->withExposedPort(80)
            ->asService()
            ->withName('svca');
    }

    public function serviceB(): Service
    {
        return $this->dag->container()
            ->from('nginx:alpine')
            ->withNewFile('/usr/share/nginx/html/index.html', ['contents' => 'Hello from Service B!'])
            ->withExposedPort(80)
            ->asService()
            ->withName('svcb');
    }

    public function services(): Service
    {
        $serviceA = $this->serviceA();
        $serviceB = $this->serviceB();
        return $this->dag->container()
            ->from('nginx:alpine')
            ->withServiceBinding('svca', $serviceA)
            ->withServiceBinding('svcb', $serviceB)
            ->withNewFile('/etc/nginx/conf.d/default.conf', [
                'contents' => '
                    server {
                        listen 80;
                        location /a {
                            proxy_pass http://svca;
                        }
                        location /b {
                            proxy_pass http://svcb;
                        }
                    }
                ',
            ])
            ->withExposedPort(80)
            ->asService();
    }
}
```

