TITLE: Implementing AI Agent in PHP
DESCRIPTION: PHP code for creating a Dagger Function that uses an LLM to solve a programming assignment. It sets up the environment, defines inputs and outputs, and interacts with the LLM to complete the task.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dagger/dagger.git/blob/main/docs/current_docs/quickstart/agent/index.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace CodingAgent;

use Dagger\Client;
use Dagger\Container;
use Dagger\Env;
use Dagger\LLMCompletion;

class CodingAgent
{
    public function goProgram(string $assignment): Container
    {
        $client = Client::connect();
        $model = $client->defaultLLMModel();

        $builder = $client->container()->from("golang:latest");

        $environment = Env::new([
            "assignment" => $assignment,
        ])->withInputs([
            "builder" => "A container used to build and run Go programs",
        ])->withOutputs([
            "completed" => "A container with the completed assignment",
        ]);

        $prompt = "You are an expert Go programmer. Your task is to write a Go program that fulfills the given assignment. Write the program, build it, and test it. If there are any errors, fix them and try again. When you are satisfied with the result, return the container with the completed assignment.";

        $result = $model->complete(LLMCompletion::new()
            ->withPrompt($prompt)
            ->withEnvironment($environment)
            ->withInputs(Env::new(["builder" => $builder->id()])));

        return $result->container("completed");
    }
}

return function (Client $client) {
    return new CodingAgent();
};
```

