DESCRIPTION: A Python Dagger function that demonstrates using terminal sessions at different points in a container pipeline to aid debugging.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dagger/dagger.git/blob/main/docs/current_docs/api/terminal.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import sys
import anyio
import dagger


async def terminal_with_container():
    async with dagger.Connection() as client:
        container = client.container().from_("alpine")

        print("Opening first terminal session")
        container = container.terminal()

        container = container.with_exec(["apk", "add", "curl"])

        print("Opening second terminal session")
        container = container.terminal()


if __name__ == "__main__":
    anyio.run(terminal_with_container)
```

