TITLE: Exposing Host Services to Dagger Functions (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: This PHP code shows how to access a MariaDB service running on the host from a Dagger Function. It defines a 'userList' method that takes a Service argument and queries the database.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dagger/dagger.git/blob/main/docs/current_docs/api/services.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace MyModule;

use Dagger\Container;
use Dagger\Module;
use Dagger\Service;

class MyModule extends Module
{
    public function userList(Service $svc): string
    {
        return $this->dag->container()
            ->from('mariadb:10.11.2')
            ->withServiceBinding('db', $svc)
            ->withEnvVariable('MYSQL_PWD', 'secret')
            ->withExec([
                'mysql',
                '-h', 'db',
                '-u', 'root',
                '-e', 'SELECT Host, User FROM mysql.user;',
                '-t',
            ])
            ->stdout();
    }
}
```

