TITLE: Mounting Directory to Container in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This PHP function mounts a specified directory to the /src path in a container and returns the modified container. It accepts a Directory argument which can reference a local filesystem directory or a remote Git repository.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dagger/dagger.git/blob/main/docs/current_docs/cookbook/cookbook.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace MyModule;

use Dagger\Container;
use Dagger\Directory;
use Dagger\Module;

#[Module]
class MyModule
{
    public function mountDirectory(Directory $source): Container
    {
        return dag()->container()->from('alpine')->withMountedDirectory('/src', $source);
    }
}
```

