TITLE: Implementing Constructor with Default Complex Type in Python for Dagger Module
DESCRIPTION: This Python code shows how to create a constructor with a default complex type (Container) for a Dagger module. It defines a MyModule class with a container attribute and a version method.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dagger/dagger.git/blob/main/docs/current_docs/api/constructors.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import dagger

@dagger.object_type
class MyModule:
    container: dagger.Container = dagger.field(default_factory=lambda: dagger.container().from_("alpine:3.14.0"))

    async def version(self) -> str:
        return await self.container.with_exec(["cat", "/etc/os-release"]).stdout()
```

