TITLE: PHP Implementation for Dagger API Client
DESCRIPTION: This PHP implementation creates a GraphQL client for the Dagger API, adds HTTP Basic authentication, and executes a query to retrieve and display the Alpine container's OS release information.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dagger/dagger.git/blob/main/docs/current_docs/api/clients-http.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

require __DIR__ . '/vendor/autoload.php';

use GraphQL\Client;
use GraphQL\Exception\QueryError;
use GraphQL\QueryBuilder\QueryBuilder;

// Get environment variables for the Dagger session
$port = getenv('DAGGER_SESSION_PORT');
$token = getenv('DAGGER_SESSION_TOKEN');

// Create HTTP headers with Basic auth
$headers = [
    'Authorization' => 'Basic ' . base64_encode("$token:"),
];

// Initialize the GraphQL client
$client = new Client(
    "http://127.0.0.1:$port/query", 
    $headers
);

// Define the GraphQL query
$query = <<<'GRAPHQL'
query {
  container {
    from(address: "alpine:latest") {
      exec(args: ["cat", "/etc/os-release"]) {
        stdout
      }
    }
  }
}
GRAPQL;

try {
    // Execute the query
    $results = $client->runRawQuery($query);
    $data = $results->getData();

    // Print the result
    echo $data->container->from->exec->stdout;
} catch (QueryError $e) {
    // Show the error message
    echo 'GraphQL query error: ' . $e->getMessage();
}
```

