TITLE: Implementing Constructor with Default Complex Type in PHP for Dagger Module
DESCRIPTION: This PHP code shows how to create a constructor with a default complex type (Container) for a Dagger module. It defines a MyModule class with a container property and a version method.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dagger/dagger.git/blob/main/docs/current_docs/api/constructors.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace App;

use Dagger\Container;
use Dagger\Function\DaggerFunction;

class MyModule
{
    public function __construct(
        #[DaggerFunction]
        private ?Container $container = null
    ) {
        $this->container ??= Container::from('alpine:3.14.0');
    }

    #[DaggerFunction]
    public function version(): string
    {
        return $this->container->withExec(['cat', '/etc/os-release'])->stdout();
    }
}
```

